Program: Outlook
Title: 20/07/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p003nvpq
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 20 Jul 2009
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Matthew Bannister. On today's programme: Birth photo arrest; Apollo 11 at 40; and Bhopal 25 years on. Zambian newspaper editor arrested Outlook hears from the newspaper editor, Chansa Kabwelawho, who was arrested for circulating pictures of a woman giving birth outside a hospital. The moon and me On the 40th anniversary of the moon landing - more of your moon memories. Bhopal 25 years on, we remember the world's worst industrial accident in Bhopal - and how it changed Sathyu Sarangi's life forever. Show less